The paper deals with deep learning applied to visual object recognition, which is a core topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The focus of the paper is on unsupervised feature learning, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also uses convolutional neural networks, which is a popular technique in neural networks (cs.NE). Finally, the paper involves image processing and classification, which is a common theme in natural language processing (cs.CL).
